# MSYS2-UWP sync project

## Purpose

Replay upstream commit history from `msys2/MSYS2-packages` and `msys2/MINGW-packages`
into `msys2-uwp/msys2-uwp` on branch `upstream`.

## Path mapping

- `msys2/MSYS2-packages` -> `ports/`
- `msys2/MINGW-packages` -> `ports-mingw/`

## Base commit

First replayed commit parents `6fc20894663468a04dd4986a8b1c15a9d5ae8649` on
`msys2-uwp/msys2-uwp`. Bootstrap/rebuild reset `upstream` to this SHA before replay.
Do not rewrite the base commit from sync tooling.

## Replay rules

- Merge pending commits by replay rank while preserving git order within each source.
- Preserve upstream author name/email and author date (`GIT_AUTHOR_*`).
- Preserve upstream committer name/email and committer date (`GIT_COMMITTER_*`).
- Author and committer metadata are never collapsed to one identity or date.
- Use normalized commit message template from `docs/PLAN.md` (Deterministic replay).
- Do not use wholesale `git merge` of upstream repos.
- Incremental runs must match append order of a full rebuild at same upstream tips.
- Incremental only: skip commits with committer date within `minReplayAgeMinutes` (default 5).
- Track replay and resume state with destination branches only (`upstream`, `upstream-ports`, `upstream-ports-mingw`); no checkpoint file (see `docs/PLAN.md`).

## Triggers

- Primary: mirror repos dispatch on push (~1-5 min after upstream).
- Fallback: hourly poll + daily reconciliation in `sync-upstream.yml`.

